[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This is a strong recipe. The problem statement is vivid and clinically grounded, the technology section teaches graph databases from first principles without vendor lock-in, and the version management discussion addresses a real operational pain point that most implementations discover too late. The recipe correctly identifies that the hard part is ETL, not the graph queries, which is honest and useful.
